# Geolocation Investigations

Identifying the location of images and videos using publicly available information, visual clues, satellite imagery, and evidence-based analysis.

This repository documents my journey in OSINT geolocation through practical investigations, methodology breakdowns, and real-world case studies.

## Areas of Focus

- Landmark Identification
- Road Sign Analysis
- Terrain & Environmental Analysis
- Architecture & Infrastructure Recognition
- Shadow & Sun Position Analysis
- Satellite Imagery Comparison
- Street View Verification
- Image-to-Map Correlation
- Video Geolocation
- Evidence Documentation & Reporting

## Investigation Methodology

1. Collect available visual evidence.
2. Extract and document identifiable clues.
3. Generate location hypotheses.
4. Verify findings using mapping and satellite tools.
5. Correlate multiple sources of evidence.
6. Document conclusions with supporting evidence.

